document_data.Known Sign Languages:
[[File:Thieves' cant.png|thumb|right|''[[Shandie Freefoot|Shandie]] and [[Krydle]] signing thieves' cant to each other.'']]
Some specific sign languages were:
* [[Common Sign Language]], which shared signs and vocabulary with thieves' cant;<ref>{{Cite adventurers league/When the Lights Went Out in Candlekeep|27}}
* [[Draconic sign language]], designed for [[dragon]]s and employed movements of jaw, claws, and wings; 
* [[Drow Sign Language]], also known as drow silent tongue;<ref><ref>{{Cite polyhedron/97/The Living City: The Hand of Mercy and Marigold's Menagerie|7-8,10-11}}
* [[Harpspeak]], used for secret communication by the [[Harpers]],<ref> known as 'silent signs'.
* [[Malatran sign language]], developed from signals used by hunters, with different systems in use across the [[Malatran Plateau]];<ref>{{Cite polyhedron/108/Jungle Lore|16}}<ref>{{Cite polyhedron/129/More Living Jungle Races|33}} and
* [[Spell Cant]], a secret sign language used only by the [[Knights of the Mystic Fire]] based on arcane spellcraft and religious lore to communicate only in metaphor, rendering it secure against ''[[comprehend languages]]''.<ref>{{Cite trumpeter/2-3|9-10}}

Some spoken languages also included signs and gestures to some degree:
* [[Alignment languages]], which each included a few certain gestures;
* [[Ruathlek]], the secret language of [[illusionist]]s, included a sign language.
* [[Thieves' cant]], which employed hand gestures alongside coded language,<ref>{{Cite comic/Legends of Baldur's Gate 2|7}}<ref>{{Cite web/theedverse/2020-05-04 - Sign Languages in the Realms}} where the signed element was known as hand cant.
